gurmukhi: ਸਤਿ ਦੁਅਾਪਰ ਤ੍ਰਿਤੀਅਾ ਕਲਿਜੁਗ ਚਤ੍ਰ ਕਾਲ ਪ੍ਰਧਾਨ ॥
transliteration: Sat(i) Duaapar Tritooaa Kal(i) Joug Charta Kaal Pradhaan||
translation: He is Supremely Pervasive in the four ages of Satyuga, Treta, Dvapara and Kaliyuga.

gurmukhi: ਧਿਅਾੲਿ ਧਿਅਾੲਿ ਥਕੇ ਮਹਾ ਮੁਨਿ ਗਾੲਿ ਗੰਧ੍ਰਬ ਅਪਾਰ ॥
transliteration: Dhiaae Dhiaae Thake Mahaa Mounni Gaae Gaddhrab Apaar||
translation: The great sages have got tired of meditating upon Him and also Infinite Gandharvas singing His Praises continuously.

gurmukhi: ਹਾਰਿ ਹਾਰਿ ਥਕੇ ਸਭੈ ਨਹੀਂ ਪਾੲੀਅੈ ਤਿਹ ਪਾਰ ॥੧੯॥੧੯੯॥
transliteration: Daar(i) Daar(i) Thake Sabhai Naheen Paaaeei Tih Paar||19||199||
translation: All have gone weary and accepted defeat, but none could know His end.19.199.

gurmukhi: ਨਾਰਦ ਅਾਦਿਕ ਬੇਦ ਬਿਅਾਸਕ ਮੁਨਿ ਮਹਾਨ ਅਨੰਤ ॥
transliteration: Naarad Aadik Bed Biaasak Mounndi) Mahaan Anant||
translation: The sage Narada and other, Ved Vyas and other and innumerable great sages;

gurmukhi: ਧਿਅਾੲਿ ਧਿਅਾੲਿ ਥਕੇ ਸਭੈ ਕਰ ਕੋਟਿ ਕਸਟ ਦੁਰੰਤ ॥
transliteration: Dhiaae Dhiaae Thake Soubhai Kar Kottee Kast Durant||
translation: Practising millions of arduous hardships and meditations all have got tired.

gurmukhi: ਗਾੲਿ ਗਾੲਿ ਥਕੇ ਗੰਧ੍ਰਬ ਨਾਚ ਅਪੱਛਰ ਅਪਾਰ ॥
transliteration: Gade Gade Thake Gaddhrab Naach Apachchhar Apaar||
translation: Gandharvas have got tired by singing and countless Apsaras (heavenly damsels) by dancing.

gurmukhi: ਸੋਧਿ ਸੋਧਿ ਥਕੇ ਸੁਰ ਪਾੲਿਓ ਨਹਿ ਪਾਰ ॥੨੦॥੨੦੦॥
transliteration: Sodh(i) Sodh(i) Thake Mahaa Sur Paaio Nah(i) Paar||20||200||
translation: The great gods have got tired in their continuous search, but they could not know His end.20.200.

gurmukhi: ੲੇਕ ਸਮੈ ਸ੍ਰੀ ਅਾਤਮਾ ੳੁਚਰਿਓ ਮਤਿ ਸਿੳੁ ਬੈਨ ॥
transliteration: Ek Samai Sri Aatmaa Ouchadio Mat(i) Sio Bain||
translation: Once the Soul spoke these words to Intellect:

gurmukhi: ਸਬ ਪ੍ਰਤਾਪ ਜਗਦੀਸ ਕੋ ਕਹੋ ਸਕਲ ਬਿਧਿ ਤੈਨ ॥੧॥੨੦੧॥
transliteration: Sah Prataap Jagdoos Ko Kaho Sakal Bidh(i) Tain||1||201||
translation: “Describe to me in every way all he Glory of the Lord of the world.” 1.201.

gurmukhi: ਕੋ ਅਾਤਮਾ ਸਰੂਪ ਹੈ ਕਹਾ ਸ੍ਰਿਸਟਿ ਕੋ ਬਿਚਾਰ ॥
transliteration: Ko Aatmaa Saroophai Kahaa Sristtee Ko Bichaar||
translation: What is the Nature of the Soul? What is the concept of the world?

gurmukhi: ਕੳੁਨ ਧਰਮ ਕੋ ਕਰਮ ਹੈ ਕਹੋ ਸਕਲ ਬਿਸਥਾਰ ॥੨॥੨੦੨॥
transliteration: Kaoun Dharam Ko Karam Hai Kaho Sakal Bisthaar||2||202||
translation: What is the object of Dharma? Tell me all in detail.2.202.
